alert.note: Alert for Southern Cook, North Shore (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 16 at 7:07PM CST until November 16 at 10:00PM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM CST THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 25 mph with gusts up to 60 mph. * WHERE...Southern Cook County. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Grand Portage Reservation. * WHEN...Until 10 PM CST this evening. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The highest gusts will be near the shores of Lake Superior along Highway 61.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
